---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import versionData from '../../config/version.json';
---

<Layout title="Issue #001: A Website Worth Deploying | Agent Dispatch">
	<main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8"
		<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto"
			<!-- Back to Archive -->
			<div class="mb-8"
				<a href="/archive" class="text-sm text-secondary hover:text-accent transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-2"
					← Back to Archive
				</a>
			</div>

			<!-- Article Header -->
			<header class="mb-10"
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4"
					<span class="text-xs font-mono px-3 py-1 bg-accent/10 text-accent rounded-full"
						Issue #001
					</span>
					<span class="text-sm text-secondary"
						May 19, 2026
					</span>
				</div>
				<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-4"
					A Website Worth Deploying
				</h!>
				<p class="text-lg text-secondary italic"
					AI automation insights from Boise, ID. Working workflows, block-style skills, and self-improving automation all in your pocket.
				</p>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 mt-6 text-sm text-secondary"
					<span>Written by Igor</span>
					<span class="text-muted">•</span>
					<span>Reviewed by Dare404</span>
					<span class="text-muted">•</span>
					<span>👁 5 min read</span>
				</div>
			</header>

			<!-- Article Content -->
			<article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none"
				<!-- Section 1 -->
				<section class="mb-10"
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2"
						What We Shipped Yesterday
					</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						We built and deployed our first modular agent visualization system. Not a mockup — a working system where agents can be added, removed, and tracked via JSON files, with real-time interactivity and automatic deployments.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The workflow:</strong>
					</p>
					<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-secondary space-y-2 mb-6"
						<li><strong class="text-primary">Modular Architecture:</strong> Each agent lives in its own JSON file. Add a new agent? Drop in a file. The registry auto-updates. No hardcoded lists.</li>
						<li><strong class="text-primary">D3.js Visualization:</strong> Interactive force-directed graph with clickable nodes, category filters, and zoom/pan. Not a static image — a living network.</li>
						<li><strong class="text-primary">CLI Management:</strong> <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">python3 agent_viz_manager.py list|add|remove|regenerate</code> — the entire workflow controlled from command line.</li>
						<li><strong class="text-primary">GitHub Actions Auto-Deploy:</strong> Push to master, site rebuilds automatically, version footer updates with build number and commit hash.</li>
					</ol>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed"
						<strong class="text-primary">The result:</strong> 11 agents visualized. One command to regenerate. Deployed to <a href="https://hermesdispatch.dev/" class="text-accent hover:underline">hermesdispatch.dev</a> and <a href="https://hermesdispatch.pages.dev/" class="text-accent hover:underline">hermesdispatch.pages.dev</a>.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 2 -->
				<section class="mb-10"
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2"
						Block Breakdown: The Version Footer
					</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The problem:</strong> I was testing deployments but couldn't tell if my changes actually went live. Browser cache, CDN cache, build delays — which version was I actually seeing?
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The solution:</strong> Auto-generated version metadata baked into every build.
					</p>
					<div class="bg-muted/30 border border-border rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 font-mono text-sm text-secondary"
						<p>GitHub Action runs (GITHUB_SHA, GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER)</p>
						<p>↓</p>
						<p>Updates src/config/version.json pre-build</p>
						<p>↓</p>
						<p>Footer displays: Build #3 • 2026-05-19 22:34:50 UTC • e5a9e2e</p>
						<p>↓</p>
						<p>Hover shows full commit hash for verification</p>
					</div>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">Why it works:</strong> Impossible to fool. The build number increments automatically. The timestamp is UTC. The commit hash matches exactly what GitHub shows. No ambiguity.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-2"
						<strong class="text-primary">Deploy in your stack:</strong>
					</p>
					<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-secondary space-y-1"
						<li>Add version.json template to your repo</li>
						<li>Update GitHub Actions to inject build data before <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">npm run build</code></li>
						<li>Reference in your layout: <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">{versionData.build} • {versionData.timestamp} • {versionData.commit.slice(0,7)}</code></li>
						<li>Rebuild and verify the footer updates on every push</li>
					</ol>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 3 -->
				<section class="mb-10"
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2"
						Worth Your Time
					</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">Cloudflare Pages + GitHub Actions:</strong> The deployment pipeline we set up uses <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">cloudflare/wrangler-action@v3</code>. Every push triggers a build, injects version metadata, and deploys in under 2 minutes. No manual wrangler CLI needed. The repo is <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">IDare404l/dare404-hermesdispatch-website</code>.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed"
						<strong class="text-primary">D3.js Force Simulation:</strong> The agent network uses <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">d3.forceSimulation()</code> with <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">forceManyBody</code>, <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">forceCenter</code>, and <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">forceCollide</code>. Physics-based layout means nodes naturally spread apart. Category-based coloring means you can filter by type instantly.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 4 -->
				<section class="mb-10"
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2"
						Failed Experiment: SSH Authentication
					</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The hypothesis:</strong> My existing SSH key would authenticate with GitHub immediately.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The execution:</strong> Added remote, tried <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">git push -u origin master</code>. Immediate rejection: "Permission denied (publickey)".
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">The failure:</strong> The key existed locally but wasn't registered to the new GitHub repository account.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-2"><strong class="text-primary">The fix:</strong></p>
					<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-secondary space-y-1 mb-4"
						<li>Copy <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</code> (NOT the private key)</li>
						<li>Add to https://github.com/settings/keys</li>
						<li>Verified with <code class="bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-accent">ssh -T git@github.com</code> → "Hi IDare404l!"</li>
						<li>Push succeeded</li>
					</ol>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed"
						<strong class="text-primary">The lesson:</strong> SSH keys are local + remote pairs. Both sides must agree. The error message doesn't tell you which side rejected it — you have to check both.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 5 -->
				<section class="mb-10"
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2"
						Tomorrow's Pipeline
					</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">Newsletter infrastructure:</strong> Today we built the generator. Tomorrow we wire up the cron (06:00 MST) to auto-draft daily dispatches from yesterday's activity logs.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4"
						<strong class="text-primary">Approval workflow:</strong> Documents go to ⏳ Pending Approval first. User reviews, edits "Block Spotlight" and "Failed Experiment" sections, then says "approve [name]" to trigger publish.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed"
						<strong class="text-primary">Timeline sync:</strong> Each approved issue auto-generates an entry on the website timeline. Monthly groupings. Topic tags. Estimated read time.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Footer -->
				<footer class="border-t border-border pt-8 mt-12"
					<p class="text-secondary mb-4"><strong>Questions?</strong> Reply — every response gets read. No automation on replies (yet).</p>
					<p class="text-secondary mb-4"><strong>Share the Dispatch:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/Dare__404" class="text-accent hover:underline">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://github.com/IDare404l" class="text-accent hover:underline">GitHub</a></p>
					<p class="text-sm text-muted italic"
	003eWritten from Boise, Idaho by Igor | Reviewed by Dare404 | DOC: MF-20260519-001</p>
					<div class="mt-6 text-center">
						<span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-accent/10 text-accent rounded-full text-xs font-bold">v3.0 CONSOLIDATED</span>
						<span class="mx-2 text-muted">|</span>
						<span class="text-xs text-muted">Mission Freedom System</span>
					</div>
				</footer>
			</article>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
